# Piral app shell rules (for AI assistants)

> Generated when this Piral instance was scaffolded. Most assistants read
> AGENTS.md (Cursor/Claude), .cursorrules, or .github/copilot-instructions.md.
> Keep this in sync as you add or remove plugins and shared dependencies.

This repository is the Piral **app shell** `<%- packageName %>` (built on
`<%- framework %>`). It is the host that loads and composes pilets at runtime.

## The contract this shell exposes to pilets

- Pilets target this shell by name and import the typed API as:
  `import type { PiletApi } from '<%- packageName %>'`.
- Pilet API plugins installed here (these define the methods pilets may call):
  <%- (plugins && plugins.length) ? plugins.join(', ') : 'none yet — add plugins to createInstance and list them here' %>.
- Centrally shared externals come from this package's `importmap` in `package.json`
  (typically `react`, `react-dom`, and e.g. `react-router-dom` or a design system).
  Pilets treat these as provided by the shell — keep the importmap accurate.
- Document the extension slot names (and their `params`) this shell renders, so
  pilet authors know what they can fill.

## Conventions

- Keep the shell thin: layout, auth, routing, shared runtime, extension registry.
  Feature logic belongs in pilets, not here.
- Configure the runtime via `createInstance` from `<%- framework %>`.
<% if (framework === 'piral') { -%>
- This shell uses `piral` (batteries-included). For the long run, consider moving to
  `piral-core` and registering plugins explicitly.
<% } else if (framework === 'piral-core') { -%>
- This shell uses `piral-core`: every plugin is registered explicitly in
  `createInstance({ plugins: [...] })`. Keep the plugin list above in sync with it.
<% } else { -%>
- This shell uses `piral-base` (the low-level, framework-agnostic loader). There is
  no React runtime or standard Pilet API here unless you add one on top.
<% } -%>
- Don't hardcode a pilet list — that's the feed service's job; the shell only knows
  the feed URL. Don't define feature routes in the shell; pilets register their own.
- Scaffold with `npm init piral-instance`; run the CLI via npm scripts or `npx`
  (`npx piral debug | build`). Never install `piral-cli` globally.
- Target React version: <%- reactVersion %>.

